article_title: Crews battle grass fire in Butler County
article_text:
Several crews are battling a large grass fire in Butler County.

Firefighters were called around 2:30 p.m. to a fire in the area of Southwest Butler Road and 14th Street, north of Rose Hill. Dispatchers said at least one shed was destroyed.

It took firefighters a little over an hour to get the fire under control. They were able to douse the flames before they reached any homes.

No injuries were reported.
